\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Pg.41}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Agnes was ridiculed for her apparently odd behavior, much like douceline of digne or francis of assisi. For example, one day witnesses saw her bowing to a basement window as she passed by. Her detractos later descovered that a stolen consecrated host had been stored there.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 In spain, similar to beguines, were the beatas - emerged around 1200. Small homes clled beaterio. Records confiscated by spanish inquisition.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Stigmata served as a direct sign of authority given by god.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The women were safe fro mrape there. Medieval women from prominent families, or who were themselves wealthy, were in danger of rape with the intent of forcing htem into a marriage. As appalling as it is to our modern sensibilities, the assailant could goto court and demand the right to marry the woman he had raped in order to \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8216\'91clear her reputation\u8217\'92.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 1242 - countess joan issued general order for baliffs to protect any and all beguines.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Aunts invited nieces, cousins to cousins, rarely were total strangers allowed to join.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Undyed wool}
