\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The church approved marriage separation if woman entered monastic life - or beguinage.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Most medieval nuns lived under some expression of the Rule of Benedict}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Slander included accusations of sexual promiscutiy and prostitution.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Any beguine found to be pregnant must be removed from the beguine community for at least a year, once her condition became eviden. The statues  allowed for the \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93fallen\u8221\'94 beguines return if her good behavior warranted this. While beguines were sensitive to behavior that compromised their ability to lead independent lives, they also realized that a \u8220\'93disgraced\u8221\'94 woman was marginalized by society and had limited opportunities to have a dignified life. By returning to her beguine community and raising her child within the buinage, a woman was saved from a forced marriage or a life of prostitution.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 P.66}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Beguines, like women in general, were not supposed to compete with men or better them in the public realm. Guilds were threatened by beguines willingness to produce for less income. Laws were enacted which effected only beguines which limited income and restricted cloth output\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8230\'85Laws were passed in many parts of europe which restricted beguine\u8217\'92s use of spindles. Any beguine found to have violated this restriction was fined, any cloth produced in this manner to be given to the poor.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Beguines in italy - untroubled by laws, developed a distinctive cloth for the poor called panni humiliati.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Statues of the Gray Sisters - earliest survivng example of women in europe proclaiming active ministry as sanctifying, as opposed to contemplative prayer being the only avenue. Permitted women to go to the sick when called.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Due to politically motivated accusations of scandalous behaviour, beguines eventually found it necessary to limit their health care to women only.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Lepers outlawed from entering towns and cities. Under Pope Alexander III, 1179-Third Lateran Council\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s Decree on Lepers - regarded Leprosy as the product of sin and sexual aberration - protected the rights of lepers to gather and form communities for mutual support and protection.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Medical care was nonexistant unless provided by Beguines.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Pg.79 Adriana Contarini and Helena Priuli - Venice.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 We have succeeded in sheltering thrity little girls, all snatched from the power of hte devil; we see thte degradation of these girl-children who, at the age of twelve or thirteen or even younger, have been sold by their own mothers; they come from all social ranks, from the nobility, the middle class, the workers. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Our times are so disastrous that no words can express the wretchedness of some of the cases.\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Marguerite Porete - see sayings}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Kindness toward others obeys no created thing but love. Kindness toward others possesses nothing over her own, and if she doe possess something, she never says it belongs to her. Kindness toward others skips her own needs to help an eighbor\u8230\'85 kindness toward others gies to ther neighborss all she has that\u8217\'92s worht anything. She keeps nothing for herself. Her amazing generostiy often makes her promis what she doesn\u8217\'92t have because she knows the more she gives, the more she receives in her soul. Kindness toward others is uch a wise businesswoman that she earns profits everywhere when others go out of business.\u8221\'94 }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Three orphan girls, lucked off the wharf and saved from the brothels to be educated and trained in cloth finishing.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The music and singing commences; the songs are lively and familiar, you happily join in. The beguines are clapping to the beat of the music and begin a gentle swaying movement. With the third song, you all enter into an informal, gentle dance, moving first toward the left and then toward the right. Feet stamp and hands sway in rhythm to the music. Soon beguines are weaving around one another in a style echoing folk dances. The church is filled with harmonious sound and mevement. The children, who had shared in the dancing, at some point tucker out and rest for a while near the elders.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab Song after song, poetic aspiration and scripture. The church interior is warm; skin glows. Eventually the activiteis quiet down and the beguines stand or sit in silence. Some of the leders light candles. The magistra climbs the steps of the pulpit and preaches.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab Like this: Always read the Book of Life, which is the life of the GOd-Man, Jesus Christ, who lived in poverty, pain, scorn and true obedience. Do not skim this book. Let it penetrat you while you read it. It will teach you everything you need to know, no matter your present circumstances. It will fill you with a burning fire that will be your greatest consolation.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab Silence. Quiet weeping by a few beguines. Others began to sing. The magista slowly moves among the praying and singing beguines. She stops here and there and lays her hands on one of the women, praying softly. Someone calls out, asking for prayer. Another beckons. At last the instruments are picked up, and the beguine begin to dance again, filling their beautiful church with joy.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Being slain in the spirit\u8221\'94 - person drops to ground in intense silence}
