\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Catherine of Genoa (1447-1510)}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Purgation and Purgatory is Catherin\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s account of her own spiritual purificaiton that she described as a fier love. .. Catherine taught that God is Pure Love and the object of our total fulfillment, but that the spiritual life as a process or journey\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 growing from self-will into pure love-is not easy and continues after our death.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93God is my being, my me, my strength, my happiness, my good, my delight\u8230\'85 I will have nothing to do with a love that would be }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 for}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  God or }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 in}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  God. I cannot bear the word }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 for}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  or the word }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 in, }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 because they denote something that may be in between God and me. Thisi s the love that pure love cannot bear since pure love is Godself.\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94}
