\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Christina Mirabilis - the astonishing - willing to be perceived as a foolif it meant people might reform their lives.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She threw herself into hot ovens, placed her hands and feet into fires, jumped into boiling cauldrons, stood in frigid waters in the dead of winter, hung herself on gibbets ,and entered tombs to preach to the dead.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Once, upon entering a church, it was reported that she threrwherself before the altar as if she were a sack of dry bones. Then, wailing bitterly, she began to beat her breast and her body most often and said, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8216\'91O miserable and wretched body! How long will you torment me, miserable as I am? What are you doing with me? Why do you keep my wretched soul in you for so long? Why do you delay me from seeing the face of Christ? When will you abandon me so that my soul can return freely to its creator? Woe to you, most miserable one! And oe to me who am united to you!\u8221\'94  She was enacting purgatory for her audience with the intent of shaking them awake to the consequences of their sinful life and illustrating what the experience of purgatory might be for them.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b1\i0\cf1 Relgiion as necessary advancement because it forces you to hate your own body, to distrust your own base, destructive instincts.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Visiting benedicting nuns at st. Catherine\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s near sint truiden - \u8220\'93suddenly and unexpectdly she would be ravished in the spirit and her body would whirl around like a hoop in a children\u8217\'92s game. She whirled around with such extreme violence that the individual limbs of her body could not be distinguished, when she had whirled around for a long time in this manner, it seemed as if se became weakend by the violence of the rolling and all her limbs grew quiet. Then there sounded between her throat and her breast a wondrous harmony that no mortal man could understand, nor could it be imitated by any artiicial instruemtn. That song of hers had only the pliancy and the tones of music. But the words of the melody, so to speak- if they coudl even be called words - sounded together incompreensibly. No sound or breath came out of her mouth or nose during this time, but a harmony of the angelic voice resound only from between her breast and throat.\u8221\'94}
